{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015oD4mXX9NJ5aGF5vxHn3jP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ã# Host Workflow Design (`host.cloche`)\n     2ã\n     3ã**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4ã**Status:** Design\n     5ã\n     6ã## Problem\n     7ã\n     8ãThe orchestrator's intake ã process ã output loop is hard-coded in Go\n     9ã(`internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`). Every project must follow the same flow:\n    10ãpull task ã generate prompt ã dispatch `develop` container run. This can't be changed\n    11ãwithout modifying Cloche itself. Projects that need different orchestration strategies\n    12ã(push to GitHub for review, group tickets into feature branches, stacked commits, etc.)\n    13ãhave no extension point.\n    14ã\n    15ã## Solution: `host.cloche`\n    16ã\n    17ãA special workflow file at `.cloche/host.cloche`. It uses the same DSL as container\n    18ãworkflow files, with one additional step type (`workflow`). Steps in this file execute\n    19ãon the **host machine**, not inside a container.\n    20ã\n    21ãThe workflow named `main` in this file becomes the per-task orchestration loop\n    22ãfor that project. The Go daemon becomes the executor of this workflow rather than the\n    23ãhard-coded logic holder.\n    24ã\n    25ã### File location\n    26ã\n    27ã```\n    28ã.cloche/host.cloche\n    29ã```\n    30ã\n    31ãIf the file does not exist, the daemon falls back to the current hard-coded behavior\n    32ã(pull task ã LLM prompt generation ã dispatch container workflow).\n    33ã\n    34ã---\n    35ã\n    36ã## DSL additions\n    37ã\n    38ã### New step type: `workflow`\n    39ã\n    40ãA step with `workflow_name` config key is a workflow-dispatch step. It dispatches a\n    41ãnamed container workflow run and blocks until that run completes.\n    42ã\n    43ã```\n    44ãstep develop {\n    45ã  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    46ã  results = [success, fail]\n    47ã}\n    48ã```\n    49ã\n    50ã`workflow_name` is added to `knownStepConfigKeys` in `domain/workflow.go`.\n    51ã\n    52ã`StepTypeWorkflow` is added to the `StepType` enum in `domain/workflow.go`.\n    53ã\n    54ãThe parser (`dsl/parser.go`) infers `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` is present\n    55ã(same pattern as `run` ã script, `prompt` ã agent).\n    56ã\n    57ã### Prompt input for `workflow` steps\n    58ã\n    59ãThe container workflow needs a prompt. By convention, a `workflow` step reads the\n    60ãprevious step's captured output file as the prompt. This is the primary data-passing\n    61ãmechanism.\n    62ã\n    63ãAn optional config key `prompt_step` overrides which step's output to read:\n    64ã```\n    65ãstep develop {\n    66ã  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    67ã  prompt_step   = \"prepare-prompt\"\n    68ã  results       = [success, fail]\n    69ã}\n    70ã```\n    71ã\n    72ã---\n    73ã\n    74ã## Step output capture\n    75ã\n    76ãEvery step in a host workflow execution writes its output (stdout of `run` steps,\n    77ãfinal response of `prompt` steps) to a file:\n    78ã\n    79ã```\n    80ã.cloche/<orch-run-id>/main/<step_name>.out\n    81ã```\n    82ã\n    83ã`<orch-run-id>` is a unique ID for this orchestration invocation, formatted the same\n    84ãway as workflow run IDs (e.g. `main-bold-hawk`).\n    85ã\n    86ãThe daemon tracks the most recently completed step's output path and passes it to the\n    87ãnext step as `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`.\n    88ã\n    89ã---\n    90ã\n    91ã## Environment variables injected into host steps\n    92ã\n    93ãAll `run` and `prompt` steps receive:\n    94ã\n    95ã| Variable | Value |\n    96ã|----------|-------|\n    97ã| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID being processed |\n    98ã| `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE` | Task summary/title |\n    99ã| `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY` | Task full body/description |\n   100ã| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory |\n   101ã| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output |\n   102ã| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the previous step's output file |\n   103ã\n   104ãFor `workflow` steps, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` is read automatically (unless `prompt_step`\n   105ãoverrides it).\n   106ã\n   107ã---\n   108ã\n   109ã## Executor: `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go`\n   110ã\n   111ãNew file. Implements the host workflow execution loop.\n   112ã\n   113ã```go\n   114ãtype HostRunner struct {\n   115ã    Dispatch  RunDispatcher      // existing: dispatches a container workflow run\n   116ã    WaitRun   RunWaiter          // new: blocks until a run ID completes, returns final state\n   117ã    AgentCmd  string             // command to invoke for prompt steps on host\n   118ã}\n   119ã\n   120ã// RunWorkflow executes the named workflow from a parsed host.cloche Workflow\n   121ã// for a single task. Returns the final result (\"done\" or \"abort\").\n   122ãfunc (r *HostRunner) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow, task ports.Task, orchRunID string) (string, error)\n   123ã```\n   124ã\n   125ãStep execution:\n   126ã\n   127ã- **`script` step** (`run` key): `exec.Command` with env vars, stdout captured to\n   128ã  `<step>.out`, stderr to `<step>.err`. Exit 0 ã `success`, non-zero ã `fail`.\n   129ã- **`agent` step** (`prompt` key): invoke `AgentCmd` on host with the prompt file\n   130ã  contents injected. Capture output. Exit 0 ã `success`, non-zero ã `fail`.\n   131ã- **`workflow` step** (`workflow_name` key): read prompt from prev step's `.out` file\n   132ã  (or `prompt_step` override), call `Dispatch`, then call `WaitRun` to block until\n   133ã  the container run completes. Map `succeeded` ã `success`, `failed`/`cancelled` ã\n   134ã  `fail`.\n   135ã\n   136ã`WaitRun` is a new port interface:\n   137ã\n   138ã```go\n   139ã// RunWaiter blocks until the run with the given ID reaches a terminal state.\n   140ãtype RunWaiter interface {\n   141ã    WaitRun(ctx context.Context, runID string) (domain.RunState, error)\n   142ã}\n   143ã```\n   144ã\n   145ãThe gRPC server / store already has `GetRun`; the waiter can poll it with backoff or\n   146ãsubscribe to the `OnRunComplete` event. A simple polling implementation (1s interval)\n   147ãis sufficient initially.\n   148ã\n   149ã---\n   150ã\n   151ã## Refactored `orchestrator.Orchestrator`\n   152ã\n   153ã`Orchestrator.Run()` is updated:\n   154ã\n   155ã**Current flow (hardcoded):**\n   156ã1. Pull ready tasks\n   157ã2. Claim task\n   158ã3. Call `promptGen.Generate(task)`\n   159ã4. Call `dispatch(workflow, projectDir, prompt)` ã runID\n   160ã5. (In-flight counter managed, `OnRunComplete` decrements it)\n   161ã\n   162ã**New flow (when `host.cloche` exists):**\n   163ã1. Pull ready tasks\n   164ã2. Claim task\n   165ã3. Parse `.cloche/host.cloche` ã find `main` workflow\n   166ã4. Generate an `orchRunID` (`main-<namegen>`)\n   167ã5. Spin up a goroutine: call `hostRunner.RunWorkflow(ctx, orch wf, task, orchRunID)`\n   168ã6. On goroutine return: decrement in-flight, update task state (success/fail)\n   169ã\n   170ãThe old `promptGen` and `dispatch` are still used as the **fallback** when\n   171ã`host.cloche` is absent (no breaking change for existing projects).\n   172ã\n   173ã`WaitRun` needs access to the run store. Wire it in `initOrchestrator` in\n   174ã`cmd/cloched/main.go`.\n   175ã\n   176ã---\n   177ã\n   178ã## Default `host.cloche` (from `cloche init`)\n   179ã\n   180ã```\n   181ã# host.cloche ã orchestration workflow (runs on host, not in container)\n   182ã# Steps here execute as the daemon user. Keep operations simple and safe.\n   183ã\n   184ãworkflow \"main\" {\n   185ã  step prepare-prompt {\n   186ã    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   187ã    results = [success, fail]\n   188ã  }\n   189ã\n   190ã  step develop {\n   191ã    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   192ã    results       = [success, fail]\n   193ã  }\n   194ã\n   195ã  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   196ã  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   197ã  develop:success        -> done\n   198ã  develop:fail           -> done\n   199ã}\n   200ã```\n   201ã\n   202ãAnd `.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` (created by init, chmod +x):\n   203ã\n   204ã```bash\n   205ã#!/usr/bin/env bash\n   206ã# Default prompt generator. Uses task env vars injected by cloched.\n   207ã# Write the prompt to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT (also echoed to stdout).\n   208ãset -euo pipefail\n   209ã\n   210ãprompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n   211ã\n   212ã${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n   213ã\n   214ãecho \"$prompt\"\n   215ã[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n   216ã```\n   217ã\n   218ã---\n   219ã\n   220ã## `.gitignore` update\n   221ã\n   222ã`cloche init` adds `.cloche/scripts/` is NOT gitignored (scripts are project config).\n   223ãThe orchestration run output dirs follow the same pattern as container run dirs:\n   224ã`.cloche/main-*/` is gitignored via the existing `.cloche/*/` rule.\n   225ã\n   226ã---\n   227ã\n   228ã## Safety notes\n   229ã\n   230ã- Host steps run with the same OS privileges as the `cloched` process.\n   231ã- No network isolation.\n   232ã- `host.cloche` should only reference scripts that are committed to the project.\n   233ã- Document that `prompt` steps in `host.cloche` invoke an LLM agent with full host\n   234ã  filesystem access ã use judiciously.\n   235ã\n   236ã---\n   237ã\n   238ã## Changes required\n   239ã\n   240ã| File | Change |\n   241ã|------|--------|\n   242ã| `internal/domain/workflow.go` | Add `StepTypeWorkflow`, add `workflow_name`/`prompt_step` to `knownStepConfigKeys` |\n   243ã| `internal/dsl/parser.go` | Infer `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` key is present |\n   244ã| `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go` | New: host workflow executor |\n   245ã| `internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go` | Refactor `Run()` to use `HostRunner` when `host.cloche` exists; fall back to current behavior otherwise |\n   246ã| `internal/ports/container.go` | Add `RunWaiter` interface |\n   247ã| `cmd/cloched/main.go` | Wire `HostRunner` into orchestrator init |\n   248ã| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Create `host.cloche` and `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` |\n   249ã"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55172401-7cfb-45c6-9eaa-fc2da58fa839","uuid":"9151fd7e-937e-4c34-bcda-6e8425bd6939","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md","content":"# Host Workflow Design (`host.cloche`)\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nThe orchestrator's intake ã process ã output loop is hard-coded in Go\n(`internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`). Every project must follow the same flow:\npull task ã generate prompt ã dispatch `develop` container run. This can't be changed\nwithout modifying Cloche itself. Projects that need different orchestration strategies\n(push to GitHub for review, group tickets into feature branches, stacked commits, etc.)\nhave no extension point.\n\n## Solution: `host.cloche`\n\nA special workflow file at `.cloche/host.cloche`. It uses the same DSL as container\nworkflow files, with one additional step type (`workflow`). Steps in this file execute\non the **host machine**, not inside a container.\n\nThe workflow named `main` in this file becomes the per-task orchestration loop\nfor that project. The Go daemon becomes the executor of this workflow rather than the\nhard-coded logic holder.\n\n### File location\n\n```\n.cloche/host.cloche\n```\n\nIf the file does not exist, the daemon falls back to the current hard-coded behavior\n(pull task ã LLM prompt generation ã dispatch container workflow).\n\n---\n\n## DSL additions\n\n### New step type: `workflow`\n\nA step with `workflow_name` config key is a workflow-dispatch step. It dispatches a\nnamed container workflow run and blocks until that run completes.\n\n```\nstep develop {\n  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n`workflow_name` is added to `knownStepConfigKeys` in `domain/workflow.go`.\n\n`StepTypeWorkflow` is added to the `StepType` enum in `domain/workflow.go`.\n\nThe parser (`dsl/parser.go`) infers `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` is present\n(same pattern as `run` ã script, `prompt` ã agent).\n\n### Prompt input for `workflow` steps\n\nThe container workflow needs a prompt. By convention, a `workflow` step reads the\nprevious step's captured output file as the prompt. This is the primary data-passing\nmechanism.\n\nAn optional config key `prompt_step` overrides which step's output to read:\n```\nstep develop {\n  workflow_name = \"develop\"\n  prompt_step   = \"prepare-prompt\"\n  results       = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step output capture\n\nEvery step in a host workflow execution writes its output (stdout of `run` steps,\nfinal response of `prompt` steps) to a file:\n\n```\n.cloche/<orch-run-id>/main/<step_name>.out\n```\n\n`<orch-run-id>` is a unique ID for this orchestration invocation, formatted the same\nway as workflow run IDs (e.g. `main-bold-hawk`).\n\nThe daemon tracks the most recently completed step's output path and passes it to the\nnext step as `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`.\n\n---\n\n## Environment variables injected into host steps\n\nAll `run` and `prompt` steps receive:\n\n| Variable | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID being processed |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE` | Task summary/title |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY` | Task full body/description |\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the previous step's output file |\n\nFor `workflow` steps, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` is read automatically (unless `prompt_step`\noverrides it).\n\n---\n\n## Executor: `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go`\n\nNew file. Implements the host workflow execution loop.\n\n```go\ntype HostRunner struct {\n    Dispatch  RunDispatcher      // existing: dispatches a container workflow run\n    WaitRun   RunWaiter          // new: blocks until a run ID completes, returns final state\n    AgentCmd  string             // command to invoke for prompt steps on host\n}\n\n// RunWorkflow executes the named workflow from a parsed host.cloche Workflow\n// for a single task. Returns the final result (\"done\" or \"abort\").\nfunc (r *HostRunner) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow, task ports.Task, orchRunID string) (string, error)\n```\n\nStep execution:\n\n- **`script` step** (`run` key): `exec.Command` with env vars, stdout captured to\n  `<step>.out`, stderr to `<step>.err`. Exit 0 ã `success`, non-zero ã `fail`.\n- **`agent` step** (`prompt` key): invoke `AgentCmd` on host with the prompt file\n  contents injected. Capture output. Exit 0 ã `success`, non-zero ã `fail`.\n- **`workflow` step** (`workflow_name` key): read prompt from prev step's `.out` file\n  (or `prompt_step` override), call `Dispatch`, then call `WaitRun` to block until\n  the container run completes. Map `succeeded` ã `success`, `failed`/`cancelled` ã\n  `fail`.\n\n`WaitRun` is a new port interface:\n\n```go\n// RunWaiter blocks until the run with the given ID reaches a terminal state.\ntype RunWaiter interface {\n    WaitRun(ctx context.Context, runID string) (domain.RunState, error)\n}\n```\n\nThe gRPC server / store already has `GetRun`; the waiter can poll it with backoff or\nsubscribe to the `OnRunComplete` event. A simple polling implementation (1s interval)\nis sufficient initially.\n\n---\n\n## Refactored `orchestrator.Orchestrator`\n\n`Orchestrator.Run()` is updated:\n\n**Current flow (hardcoded):**\n1. Pull ready tasks\n2. Claim task\n3. Call `promptGen.Generate(task)`\n4. Call `dispatch(workflow, projectDir, prompt)` ã runID\n5. (In-flight counter managed, `OnRunComplete` decrements it)\n\n**New flow (when `host.cloche` exists):**\n1. Pull ready tasks\n2. Claim task\n3. Parse `.cloche/host.cloche` ã find `main` workflow\n4. Generate an `orchRunID` (`main-<namegen>`)\n5. Spin up a goroutine: call `hostRunner.RunWorkflow(ctx, orch wf, task, orchRunID)`\n6. On goroutine return: decrement in-flight, update task state (success/fail)\n\nThe old `promptGen` and `dispatch` are still used as the **fallback** when\n`host.cloche` is absent (no breaking change for existing projects).\n\n`WaitRun` needs access to the run store. Wire it in `initOrchestrator` in\n`cmd/cloched/main.go`.\n\n---\n\n## Default `host.cloche` (from `cloche init`)\n\n```\n# host.cloche ã orchestration workflow (runs on host, not in container)\n# Steps here execute as the daemon user. Keep operations simple and safe.\n\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n```\n\nAnd `.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` (created by init, chmod +x):\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Default prompt generator. Uses task env vars injected by cloched.\n# Write the prompt to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT (also echoed to stdout).\nset -euo pipefail\n\nprompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n\n${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n\necho \"$prompt\"\n[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## `.gitignore` update\n\n`cloche init` adds `.cloche/scripts/` is NOT gitignored (scripts are project config).\nThe orchestration run output dirs follow the same pattern as container run dirs:\n`.cloche/main-*/` is gitignored via the existing `.cloche/*/` rule.\n\n---\n\n## Safety notes\n\n- Host steps run with the same OS privileges as the `cloched` process.\n- No network isolation.\n- `host.cloche` should only reference scripts that are committed to the project.\n- Document that `prompt` steps in `host.cloche` invoke an LLM agent with full host\n  filesystem access ã use judiciously.\n\n---\n\n## Changes required\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `internal/domain/workflow.go` | Add `StepTypeWorkflow`, add `workflow_name`/`prompt_step` to `knownStepConfigKeys` |\n| `internal/dsl/parser.go` | Infer `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` key is present |\n| `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go` | New: host workflow executor |\n| `internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go` | Refactor `Run()` to use `HostRunner` when `host.cloche` exists; fall back to current behavior otherwise |\n| `internal/ports/container.go` | Add `RunWaiter` interface |\n| `cmd/cloched/main.go` | Wire `HostRunner` into orchestrator init |\n| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Create `host.cloche` and `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` |\n","numLines":249,"startLine":1,"totalLines":249}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01X79xamPPLkTMA3u87p468N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Awb3R57dzu7TQwyZfArQZn","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2744,"cache_read_input_tokens":14464,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2744},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55172401-7cfb-45c6-9eaa-fc2da58fa839","uuid":"76696682-a890-4177-8ec6-c97acc5e5086"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Awb3R57dzu7TQwyZfArQZn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ã# Cloche Usage\n     2ã\n     3ãCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4ãworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5ãcontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6ãresults to a git branch.\n     7ã\n     8ã## Core Concepts\n     9ã\n    10ã- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11ã- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12ã- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13ã- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14ã- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15ã\n    16ã## Workflow DSL\n    17ã\n    18ãWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19ãdeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20ãno orphans, entry point exists).\n    21ã\n    22ã### Minimal Example\n    23ã\n    24ã```\n    25ãworkflow \"develop\" {\n    26ã  step implement {\n    27ã    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28ã    results = [success, fail]\n    29ã  }\n    30ã\n    31ã  step test {\n    32ã    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33ã    results = [success, fail]\n    34ã  }\n    35ã\n    36ã  implement:success -> test\n    37ã  implement:fail -> abort\n    38ã  test:success -> done\n    39ã  test:fail -> abort\n    40ã}\n    41ã```\n    42ã\n    43ã### Step Configuration\n    44ã\n    45ã| Key | Type | Description |\n    46ã|-----|------|-------------|\n    47ã| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48ã| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49ã| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50ã| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51ã| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52ã| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53ã| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54ã| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55ã| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56ã| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57ã\n    58ãA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59ã\n    60ã### The `file()` Function\n    61ã\n    62ã`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63ã(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64ãtemplates:\n    65ã\n    66ã```\n    67ãprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68ã```\n    69ã\n    70ã### The `container {}` Block\n    71ã\n    72ãCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73ã\n    74ã**Step level** ã per-step container config:\n    75ã```\n    76ãstep code {\n    77ã  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78ã  container {\n    79ã    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80ã    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81ã    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82ã  }\n    83ã  results = [success, fail]\n    84ã}\n    85ã```\n    86ã\n    87ã**Workflow level** ã defaults for all steps:\n    88ã```\n    89ãworkflow \"develop\" {\n    90ã  container {\n    91ã    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92ã    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93ã    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94ã  }\n    95ã  ...\n    96ã}\n    97ã```\n    98ã\n    99ãSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100ã\n   101ã### Wiring Syntax\n   102ã\n   103ãConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   104ã\n   105ã```\n   106ãimplement:success -> test\n   107ãimplement:fail -> abort\n   108ãtest:success -> done\n   109ãtest:fail -> fix\n   110ã```\n   111ã\n   112ã### Wire Output Mappings\n   113ã\n   114ãExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   115ã\n   116ã```\n   117ãstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   118ã```\n   119ã\n   120ãPath expressions:\n   121ã\n   122ã| Expression | Meaning |\n   123ã|---|---|\n   124ã| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   125ã| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   126ã| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   127ã| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   128ã| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   129ã\n   130ãIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   131ãtext, only bare `output` works.\n   132ã\n   133ã### Retry Loops\n   134ã\n   135ãWire failures back to earlier steps:\n   136ã\n   137ã```\n   138ãtest:fail -> fix\n   139ãfix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   140ãfix:fail -> abort\n   141ã```\n   142ã\n   143ãUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   144ã\n   145ã```\n   146ãstep fix {\n   147ã  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   148ã  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   149ã  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   150ã}\n   151ã```\n   152ã\n   153ã### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   154ã\n   155ãWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   156ã\n   157ã```\n   158ãtest:success -> lint\n   159ãtest:success -> quality\n   160ã```\n   161ã\n   162ã### Collect (Join)\n   163ã\n   164ãSynchronize parallel branches:\n   165ã\n   166ã```\n   167ãcollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   168ãcollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   169ã```\n   170ã\n   171ã`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   172ã\n   173ã### Comments\n   174ã\n   175ãLine comments with `//`:\n   176ã\n   177ã```\n   178ã// This is a comment\n   179ãimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   180ã```\n   181ã\n   182ã## Result Protocol\n   183ã\n   184ãSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   185ã\n   186ã```\n   187ãCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   188ã```\n   189ã\n   190ãFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   191ã\n   192ãRules:\n   193ã- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   194ã- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   195ã- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   196ã- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   197ã- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   198ã\n   199ã## Prompt Assembly\n   200ã\n   201ãWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   202ã\n   203ã1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   204ã2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   205ã3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   206ã4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   207ã\n   208ãThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   209ã\n   210ã## Agent Command Resolution\n   211ã\n   212ãPriority (highest to lowest):\n   213ã1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   214ã2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }`\n   215ã3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   216ã4. Default: `claude`\n   217ã\n   218ã### Fallback Chains\n   219ã\n   220ãComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   221ã\n   222ã```\n   223ãagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   224ã```\n   225ã\n   226ã- **Command not found / failed to start** ã try next command\n   227ã- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ã try next command\n   228ã- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ã use that result (no fallback)\n   229ã- **Exit 0** ã use result (no fallback)\n   230ã- **All commands fail to start** ã step returns an error\n   231ã- **Last command crashes without marker** ã step returns `fail`\n   232ã\n   233ãKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   234ã\n   235ã## Workflow Locations\n   236ã\n   237ã**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   238ãvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   239ã\n   240ã**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   241ãSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   242ãdispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   243ãexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   244ãfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   245ã\n   246ã### Host Workflow Example\n   247ã\n   248ã```\n   249ãworkflow \"main\" {\n   250ã  step ready-tasks {\n   251ã    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n   252ã    results = [success, fail]\n   253ã  }\n   254ã\n   255ã  step prepare-prompt {\n   256ã    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   257ã    results = [success, fail]\n   258ã  }\n   259ã\n   260ã  step develop {\n   261ã    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   262ã    results       = [success, fail]\n   263ã  }\n   264ã\n   265ã  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n   266ã    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n   267ã    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n   268ã    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n   269ã  ]\n   270ã  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n   271ã  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [ CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id ]\n   272ã  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   273ã  develop:success        -> done\n   274ã  develop:fail           -> done\n   275ã}\n   276ã```\n   277ã\n   278ã### Host Step Environment Variables\n   279ã\n   280ã| Variable | Description |\n   281ã|----------|-------------|\n   282ã| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   283ã| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   284ã| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   285ã| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings (e.g. `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`). |\n   286ã\n   287ã### Container Environment Variables\n   288ã\n   289ã| Variable | Description |\n   290ã|----------|-------------|\n   291ã| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   292ã| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   293ã| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   294ã\n   295ã## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   296ã\n   297ã```\n   298ãworkflow \"develop\" {\n   299ã  step implement {\n   300ã    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   301ã    results = [success, fail]\n   302ã  }\n   303ã\n   304ã  step test {\n   305ã    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   306ã    results = [success, fail]\n   307ã  }\n   308ã\n   309ã  step lint {\n   310ã    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   311ã    results = [success, fail]\n   312ã  }\n   313ã\n   314ã  step quality {\n   315ã    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   316ã    results = [success, fail]\n   317ã  }\n   318ã\n   319ã  step fix {\n   320ã    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   321ã    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   322ã    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   323ã  }\n   324ã\n   325ã  implement:success -> test\n   326ã  implement:fail -> abort\n   327ã\n   328ã  test:success -> lint\n   329ã  test:success -> quality\n   330ã  test:fail -> fix\n   331ã\n   332ã  lint:fail -> fix\n   333ã  quality:fail -> fix\n   334ã  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   335ã\n   336ã  fix:success -> test\n   337ã  fix:fail -> abort\n   338ã  fix:give-up -> abort\n   339ã}\n   340ã```\n   341ã\n   342ã## Container Isolation Model\n   343ã\n   344ã- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   345ã- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   346ã- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n   347ã- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   348ã- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   349ã\n   350ãYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n   351ã\n   352ã## CLI Reference\n   353ã\n   354ã### `cloche init`\n   355ã\n   356ãScaffold a new Cloche project.\n   357ã\n   358ã```\n   359ãcloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   360ã```\n   361ã\n   362ã| Flag | Default | Description |\n   363ã|------|---------|-------------|\n   364ã| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   365ã| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   366ã\n   367ãCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   368ãhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   369ã\n   370ã### `cloche run`\n   371ã\n   372ãLaunch a workflow run.\n   373ã\n   374ã```\n   375ãcloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   376ã```\n   377ã\n   378ã| Flag | Description |\n   379ã|------|-------------|\n   380ã| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   381ã| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   382ã| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   383ã| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   384ã\n   385ãMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   386ãwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   387ã\n   388ã### `cloche status`\n   389ã\n   390ã```\n   391ãcloche status <run-id>\n   392ã```\n   393ã\n   394ãShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   395ã\n   396ã### `cloche list`\n   397ã\n   398ã```\n   399ãcloche list [--all]\n   400ã```\n   401ã\n   402ãLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n   403ã\n   404ã### `cloche logs`\n   405ã\n   406ã```\n   407ãcloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n   408ã```\n   409ã\n   410ã| Flag | Description |\n   411ã|------|-------------|\n   412ã| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   413ã| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   414ã| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n   415ã\n   416ãFor active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n   417ã\n   418ã### `cloche poll`\n   419ã\n   420ã```\n   421ãcloche poll <run-id>\n   422ã```\n   423ã\n   424ãBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   425ã\n   426ã### `cloche stop`\n   427ã\n   428ã```\n   429ãcloche stop <run-id>\n   430ã```\n   431ã\n   432ã### `cloche delete`\n   433ã\n   434ã```\n   435ãcloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   436ã```\n   437ã\n   438ãDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   439ã\n   440ã### `cloche health`\n   441ã\n   442ã```\n   443ãcloche health\n   444ã```\n   445ã\n   446ãShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   447ã\n   448ã### `cloche shutdown`\n   449ã\n   450ã```\n   451ãcloche shutdown\n   452ã```\n   453ã\n   454ã## Project Layout\n   455ã\n   456ã```\n   457ãmy-project/\n   458ãããã .cloche/\n   459ãã   ããã develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   460ãã   ããã host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   461ãã   ããã Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   462ãã   ããã config.toml           # Project configuration\n   463ãã   ããã prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   464ãã   ã   ããã implement.md\n   465ãã   ã   ããã fix.md\n   466ãã   ã   ããã update-docs.md\n   467ãã   ããã scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   468ãã   ããã overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   469ãã   ã   ããã CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   470ãã   ããã <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   471ãã       ããã prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   472ãã       ããã output/\n   473ãã       ã   ããã full.log      # Unified log\n   474ãã       ã   ããã test.log      # Per-step script output\n   475ãã       ã   ããã llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   476ãã       ããã attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   477ãã       ããã history.log       # Step execution log\n   478ãããã src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   479ãããã .git/\n   480ã```\n   481ã\n   482ã## Daemon Configuration\n   483ã\n   484ã| Variable | Default | Description |\n   485ã|----------|---------|-------------|\n   486ã| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   487ã| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   488ã| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   489ã| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   490ã| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   491ã| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   492ã| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   493ã| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   494ã| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   495ã| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   496ã\n   497ã### Client Configuration\n   498ã\n   499ã| Variable | Default | Description |\n   500ã|----------|---------|-------------|\n   501ã| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   502ã| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   503ã\n   504ã## Dockerfile Requirements\n   505ã\n   506ãThe container image must have:\n   507ã- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   508ã- `git` installed\n   509ã- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   510ã- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   511ã- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   512ã\n   513ã## Build Commands\n   514ã\n   515ã```\n   516ãmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   517ãmake test           # Run all tests\n   518ãmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   519ãmake lint           # Run go vet\n   520ãmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   521ãmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   522ãmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   523ãmake clean          # Remove bin/\n   524ã```\n   525ã"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55172401-7cfb-45c6-9eaa-fc2da58fa839","uuid":"f1e76922-62b0-467b-91f9-4caa225abb82","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"# Cloche Usage\n\nCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\nworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\ncontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\nresults to a git branch.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\ndeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\nno orphans, entry point exists).\n\n### Minimal Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n### Step Configuration\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n\nA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n\n### The `file()` Function\n\n`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\ntemplates:\n\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n\n### The `container {}` Block\n\nCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n\n**Step level** ã per-step container config:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow level** ã defaults for all steps:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n\n### Wiring Syntax\n\nConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\n```\n\n### Wire Output Mappings\n\nExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nPath expressions:\n\n| Expression | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n\nIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\ntext, only bare `output` works.\n\n### Retry Loops\n\nWire failures back to earlier steps:\n\n```\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test    // retry the test\nfix:fail -> abort\n```\n\nUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n\n```\nstep fix {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n  max_attempts = \"2\"\n  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n\nWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\n```\n\n### Collect (Join)\n\nSynchronize parallel branches:\n\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\ncollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n\n### Comments\n\nLine comments with `//`:\n\n```\n// This is a comment\nimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n```\n\n## Result Protocol\n\nSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\nFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n\nRules:\n- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n\n## Prompt Assembly\n\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n\n1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n\nThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n\n## Agent Command Resolution\n\nPriority (highest to lowest):\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }`\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n### Fallback Chains\n\nComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n\n```\nagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n```\n\n- **Command not found / failed to start** ã try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ã try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ã use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** ã use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** ã step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** ã step returns `fail`\n\nKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n\n## Workflow Locations\n\n**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\nvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n\n**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\nSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\ndispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\nexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\nfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n\n### Host Workflow Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n    CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n    CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n  ]\n  ready-tasks:fail       -> abort\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop [ CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output.task_id ]\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n```\n\n### Host Step Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings (e.g. `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`). |\n\n### Container Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n\n## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step lint {\n    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step quality {\n    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n\n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n## Container Isolation Model\n\n- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n\nYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n\n## CLI Reference\n\n### `cloche init`\n\nScaffold a new Cloche project.\n\n```\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n\nCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\nhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n\n### `cloche run`\n\nLaunch a workflow run.\n\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n\nFor active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche shutdown`\n\n```\ncloche shutdown\n```\n\n## Project Layout\n\n```\nmy-project/\nããã .cloche/\nã   ããã develop.cloche        # Container workflow\nã   ããã host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\nã   ããã Dockerfile            # Container image definition\nã   ããã config.toml           # Project configuration\nã   ããã prompts/              # Prompt templates\nã   ã   ããã implement.md\nã   ã   ããã fix.md\nã   ã   ããã update-docs.md\nã   ããã scripts/              # Host-side scripts\nã   ããã overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\nã   ã   ããã CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\nã   ããã <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\nã       ããã prompt.txt        # User prompt\nã       ããã output/\nã       ã   ããã full.log      # Unified log\nã       ã   ããã test.log      # Per-step script output\nã       ã   ããã llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\nã       ããã attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\nã       ããã history.log       # Step execution log\nããã src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\nããã .git/\n```\n\n## Daemon Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n\n## Dockerfile Requirements\n\nThe container image must have:\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n\n## Build Commands\n\n```\nmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\nmake test           # Run all tests\nmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\nmake lint           # Run go vet\nmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\nmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\nmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\nmake clean          # Remove bin/\n```\n","numLines":525,"startLine":1,"totalLines":525}}}
